Approach:-
Use sliding window with two pointers.
- Expand the right pointer and count characters (a, b, c).
- When the current window contains all three characters, it means all substrings ending from right to the end are valid.
- Add n - right to the answer.
- Shrink the window from the left to find more valid substrings.
Code:-
class Solution(object):
    def numberOfSubstrings(self, s):
        n = len(s)
        count = [0, 0, 0]
        left = 0
        ans = 0

        for right in range(n):
            count[ord(s[right]) - ord('a')] += 1

            while count[0] > 0 and count[1] > 0 and count[2] > 0:
                ans += n - right
                count[ord(s[left]) - ord('a')] -= 1
                left += 1

        return ans 

Time Complexity : O(n)
Space Complexity : O(1)
